<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFF3FFD8FF8DFC0BFC82FB54" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF3FFD8FF8DFC0BFF62FB14" blockId="41.[113,1092,1005,1316]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FF8DFC0BFF5EFBB4" bold="true" box="[113,224,1005,1028]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF3FFD8FF15FC0BFE1DFBB4" author="CHAMPION" box="[233,419,1005,1028]" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION (1894)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FDE0FC0BFD42FBB4" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[540,764,1005,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perampla">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FDE0FC0BFD42FBB4" box="[540,764,1005,1028]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Physonota perampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from series of 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFF3FFD8FC55FC0BFBFEFBB4" box="[937,1088,1005,1028]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
and stated that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FEEDFBEBFE55FB94" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1877" box="[273,491,1037,1060]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FEEDFBEBFE55FB94" box="[273,491,1037,1060]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Physonota pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘about equals it in size; but differs in several particulars from the insect here described [
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FE46FBCBFD86FBF4" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[442,568,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perampla">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FE46FBCBFD86FBF4" box="[442,568,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">P. perampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]’. Both taxa were only listed in catalogues except 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF3FFD8FF8DFBABFE96FBD4" author="BOROWIEC" box="[113,296,1101,1124]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" pagination="43 - 138" refId="ref48380" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2002: New records of Neotropical Cassidinae, with description of three new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Genus 13: 43 - 138." type="journal article" year="2002">BOROWIEC (2002)</bibRefCitation>
who recorded 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FE34FBABFDF7FBD4" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[456,585,1101,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perampla">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FE34FBABFDF7FBD4" box="[456,585,1101,1124]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">P. perampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as new to 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFF3FFD8FD40FBABFC97FBD4" box="[700,809,1101,1124]" name="Colombia" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. I have examined 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFF3FFD8FC17FBABFB9DFBD4" box="[1003,1059,1101,1124]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa and they are identical with no difference hence I synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FC93FB8BFC51FB34" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[879,1007,1133,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perampla">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FC93FB8BFC51FB34" box="[879,1007,1133,1156]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">P. perampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FBD1FB8BFF6AFB14" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FBD1FB8BFF6AFB14" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">P. pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF3FFD8FF6CFB4BFC82FB54" blockId="41.[113,1092,1005,1316]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">
I was unable to locate the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFF3FFD8FE4DFB4BFDBAFB74" box="[433,516,1197,1220]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">syntype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFF3FFD8FDB5FB4BFD7EFB74" box="[585,704,1197,1220]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
in the BMNH collections although Champion explicitly stated that it came from the museum material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
